#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/vertex_paint/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"Vertex Painting is a simple way of painting color onto an object, by "
"directly manipulating the color of vertices, rather than textures, and is"
" fairly straightforward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/vertex_paint/introduction.rst:10
msgid ""
"When a vertex is painted, the color of the vertex is modified according "
"to the settings of the brush. The color of all visible planes and edges "
"attached to the vertex are then modified with a gradient to the color of "
"the other connected vertices. Note that the color of occluded faces is "
"not modified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/vertex_paint/introduction.rst:15
msgid ""
"Vertex colors can be painted by switching to *Vertex Paint Mode*; "
"however, it will not show up in the render unless you check *Vertex Color"
" Paint* in the :doc:`Materials Options "
"</render/blender_render/materials/properties/options>` panel (for Blender"
" Renderer). You can also the use "
":doc:`/render/blender_render/materials/nodes/types/input/geometry` to "
"access vertex color information in the material node tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/vertex_paint/introduction.rst:21
msgid ""
